      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is fundamentally rooted in the idea that the Constitution is a fixed document, not a living text subject to modern political whims. Proponents argue that the Founders intended specific meanings for the words they chose, and judges must adhere to those original public understandings. This approach prevents unelected judges from imposing their personal, evolving policy preferences onto the law. Therefore, originalism ensures constitutional stability and fidelity to the democratic will of the time.",
